  "body": "_Part of #9264 keycard sign in epic (mark as checked there, when closing this issue)_\n\nWe should display the number of attempts if it's less than three to warn the user. The number of attempts **should be displayed after the \"Wrong passcode\" message** flashes, not overlap it. A video of how it should work is below.\n\nPlease notice that the \"2 wrong attempts\" error is fired **200ms after** the \"Wrong passcode\" animation **has started hiding**\n\n<img width=\"375\" alt=\"ыскуут\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3115606/68083697-c236c780-fe66-11e9-818b-05f9e5815226.gif\">\n\nFigma:\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/dEIljL7UPbXgsZUA0Q4qlE5E/Onboarding?node-id=4566%3A12\n\n---\n\n**Bonus**\nIt would be even cooler and a much better experience for the user if we add a more verbose warning when there's only one attempt left, with \"Help\" link in it to open a popup explaining what a \"Frozen key\" is. This could be the next iteration of this issue. cc @guylouis \n\nImage:\n<img width=\"425\" alt=\"last-attempt\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3115606/67837499-26395300-fb2a-11e9-8243-948f942b9930.png\">",
